HEADWORD: Descendent
<hw>De*scend"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>descendens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>descendre</ets>. Cf. <er>Descendant</er>.]</ety> <def>Descending;
falling; proceeding from an ancestor or source.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More than mortal grace⟦br⟧
